{
  "title": "Contextual Bandits for Recommendation Systems",
  "summary": "This document explores the application of Contextual Bandits (CB) in recommendation systems. It details how CB models can learn to optimize recommendations by considering user context and historical interactions. The process involves defining the context, selecting an appropriate bandit algorithm, and iteratively improving the recommendation strategy through exploration and exploitation.",
